I'm a level 14 High Elf mage wondering if there are any quests I should be working on now, I know it's too early for the focus items, but I was wondering if there was some quest to get a better weapon or armor (for me or the pet). I currently use a cracked staff myself, and summon staff of tracing for pet. I've made my own raw silk armor via the joys of tailoring. Any advice?<br>
Also, I want to get the new Luclin spell for pet shield, is it safe to port from GFAY and run to Shadow Haven at my level?<br>
Thank you for any input.<br>
Qeldarn<br>
HE Mage<br>
TORVONNILOUS<br>
<br>
p.s. okay, I just saw the other thread about this same topic, so I'll be reading that too, sorry for the similar topic! <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uschwab34.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Schwab34</A> at: 1/10/02 3:50:08 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uharrije.showPublicProfile?language=EN>harrije</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#333333>(1/10/02 4:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=872.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage quests in teen levels?</span><hr size=1> Most of the valuable pre-Sol Temple quests are really generic quests, i.e. they are not class specific. If you are fighting in Crushbone, for example, you can work on the orc belt quest to raise money and faction.<br>
<br>
I know of at least one minor staff quest originating in the Erudin wizard guild; one of the guildmasters will send you to Everfrost to collect some ice goblin beads. The staff is not great by any means (I think our summons are better), but if you enjoy questing you might look into it.<br>
<br>
For magicians, the first really worthwhile class-specific quests are the eight originating in the Temple of Solusek Ro. You can start looking towards these now, because it will not be many more levels before you can begin hunting for some of the components. Doing the aforementioned &quot;money and faction&quot; quests will help you pay for the expensive gems and possibly merchant-farm some of the miscellaneous quest ingredients.<br>
<br>
You will not have to do any fighting to get from Greater Faydark to the Shadowhaven merchants. The Nexus is a non-combat zone, and Shadowhaven is a neutral city. I did not have to do the faction quests in order to purchase my Luclin spells, but if you do, you should be able to complete them without having to enter combat. Just ask for a guide through Echo Caverns, and try to make sure invisibility does not fade. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uxymryk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xymryk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 120<br> <font color=#333333>(1/10/02 7:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=872.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage quests in teen levels?</span><hr size=1> If you enjoy doing quests the first wo you can do for useful items would probably begin in Qeynos. <br>
<br>
Cubert/Missing Dress Quest<br>
The Cubert quest is easilly do-able at level 14, and you might even make a little experience.  What you will need to do isdrop down into the Qeynos Catacombs and hunt for Cubert.  If you hunt down the details of the quest you will find maps showing where he spawns.  The only thing to really watch out for when you're down there is the Necro guild.  If you get to close you'll be killed.  <br>
<br>
The reward for this quest if you are lucky is a +3 Int earring.<br>
<br>
Band of Rodcet Nife Quest<br>
Another quest that is doable at your level is the quest for the band of Rodcet Nife.  This quest is easy but requires quite a bit of travel.  The way I did it only gave positive faction.  <br>
<br>
What I did was I went to the General in Surefall and received Nitrates.  Then I took the Nitrates to the zoo keeper in Ak Anon.  He's located down below the zoo.  In exchange for the Nitrates he gave me a potion of regurgentonics. (spelling).  I took the potion of regurgentoics to frosty in West Karana and he gave me a fish.  I then returned the fish to the guy swimming in the pool by the temple of Rodcet Nife.  <br>
<br>
To do the Rodcet Nife Quest you need good faction with the temple of Rodcet Nife, so you might want to do the bandit Sash quest multiple times to raise your faction first. <br>
<br>
The reward for this quest is the ring of Rodcet Nife.  A +3 Int +10 mana ring.<br>
<br>
Now in the amount of time it takes you to do either of these quests you can make enough money to buy items of similar worth several times over.  However if you enjoy doing quests or just want to try some you might want to look into them further. <p><br>
